employment.description_of_duties:
Project acquisition
• Market analysis and opportunity identification;
• Networking and proactive and strategic collaboration with donors, clients and experts;
• Evaluation of project opportunities on the basis of key figures and contextual information.
• Organizing and conducting fact-finding missions, capture planning and strategy preparation;
• Conceptual and methodical preparation of "pre-qualification" documents;
• Bid preparation and bid management of technical proposals for key tenders including but not limited to EU service contracts;
• As part of bid management, coordination of the bid team and identification of partners and experts together with the recruitment team, drafting and editing of assigned sections of the technical offer, supervision and management of external consultants and proposal writers, project design and budget development in close coordination with the finance team;
• quality assurance and timely approvals for bid development and submission.

Project management and backstopping
• Backstopping of projects in accordance with GIZ policies and procedures as well as client requirements, including but not limited to the EU PRAG guidelines;
• Support to the identification and mobilization of long- and short-term experts and planned consultancy missions in close cooperation with GIZ's recruitment team;
• Preparation, review, and quality assurance of project reports and deliverables;
• Project management and administration in accordance with GIZ and client policies and procedures;
• Management of core project processes such as planning, financial steering and procurement in close coordination with core process support teams in Ethiopia and Germany;
• Knowledge management and development of project implementation strategies;
• Management of relationships and communications with clients, partners, and experts.
